e wrong.  I am too lazy to go check myself)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Skrimgeour Kuchenhyrst</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">One problem Lanse, Naleldar is level 17 and is 29 levels (including 4 hell levels) away from ANY EM Armor....<P>I too don;t want to rehash old posts - but realistically, bronze is good but heavy - and you should definitely look for a Charred Guardian Shield and savants cap and/or runed circlet.<P>Skrimgeour Kuchenhyrst<BR>46th Level Vicar of Mithaniel Marr<BR>The Haven<BR>Karana</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Lanse</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">He did ask for "best" equipment didn't he?  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif"><P>  You can always find a few friends to walk you through Guk and hope to get some shin armor. <BR>  I found that as a high elf, that did NOT anger any frogloks in all my years, I'm not KoS to any live frogs. (So just wait at a zone and have someone give you the /loc of some shin armor.)<P>Basically free steel gloves and legs. =)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aralyn</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Im a 13th Level Cleric on Mithaniel Marr and wonder what Cleric armor I should start looking for at my level. What brought this to mind is my 14 Paladin friend who is telling me all about how he almost missed his chance at the Armor of Ro because of his faction standing.<P>Is there something I should be looking for in zones that everything doesn't con red in?<P>I feel a little overwhelmed here at the number of items I am reading about on this site and my EQ buddys "IRL" do not have any clerics so they have no idea what I should be looking for.<P>A cp for your thoughts?  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/tongue.gif"><P>------------------<BR>      ~*~Aralyn~*~<BR>http://www.pixiechild.com</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Nizdaar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">If there is a "Best" suit, then it's specific to a certain race, probably even individual, as we all allocated our points into different places.<P>------------------<BR>Nizdaar<BR>46 High-Elf Cleric<BR>Innoruuk Server<BR> <A HREF="http://www.maximumeq.com" TARGET=_blank>http://www.maximumeq.com</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Chaotic-Order</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well for a mid level cleric (20s to 30s) here is what is best and it is EVEN attainable solo or at most with a small group or you can probably shop around and buy. (Caution spoilers may be here, and I am posting this off the top of my head while servers down so some things may be wrong)<BR>Head: Runed Circlet from perma or buy it for 600pp (4wis, 4AC)<BR>Neck: Black Iron Medalion from Runny Eye or buy it for 20 pp (3 wis)<BR>Face, ear, rings: call a good jeweler shop around to several, save up and buy all at once if you can for a big deal and discount silver ruby veil for the wis and str, jasper ear and rings, you should be able to buy all FIVE items for about 1000pp to 1500pp.<BR>Arms, hands, chest, boots: do the sol temple cleric quests.  Or you can buy all those pieces for about 2500 to 3000pp or do em yourself for about 700pp and 20 hours work if you are lucky.<BR>Wrist: Cleric armor still great but always camped and farmed, go with polished bone off evil eyes in the gorge, chipped bone bracer off ogres in west karana, or runed mithril from solb off king (need a big group).  You can buy them for about 75pp PBB, 600 CBB, 800 RMB, 800 cleric only bracers.<BR>Shoulders: ademantium epols buy em for 400pp<BR>Waist: just take your pick lots of good belts<BR>legs: silver plated legs from lower guk buy em for 1000pp. Or gator leggings from upper guk for 500pp if you need the wis.<BR>For the shield go with charred out of sola, paw of opalla is hard to beat for main hand or cleric quest mace or summon yourself a hammer, for range slot do the kerren toy quest for some extra ac and agi.<BR>You may want to substitute dwarven work boots from unrest for cleric only ones.  <P>Side note here, I am a level 50 and my guild is small so while i do go to planes its usually fear or hate with an uber guild and i get no loot, so EVERY item I have I have gotten solo or traded for it without exception.  EVERY PIECE SOLO WITH MY CLERIC OR at most with one other and it hasn't changed much in about 15 levels.  I think what I have is pretty good  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif">.  I do now have a forest loop after 2 levels hehe. <A HREF="http://home.cybersouth.com/dkight/chaocle.GIF" TARGET=_blank>http://home.cybersouth.com/dkight/chaocle.GIF</A> <P>Chaocle Orderic<BR>Chaotic-Order website at <A HREF="http://www.chaotic-order.com" TARGET=_blank>www.chaotic-order.com</A> <BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Creadance</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Chaotic-Order I dont know what server you are on but If you are paying those prices for those items your a fool on Bertoxx these are the cost of those items:<BR>Runed Circlet: around 300plat these days<BR>Black Iron Medalion: around 20plat<BR>Plat Jasper Rings: 500 plat for 2 of them<BR>Plat Ruby Veil: around 800 plat <BR>Electrom Jasper Earring: Dont know <BR>Adamantite Epolets: around 300 these days<P>The rest seam about right <BR>But ill never buy cleric quest armor for 2k or even 3k its easy to get them now adays with guild members and friends.<BR><P>------------------<BR>50th Level Dwarven Cleric<BR>Member of the Jesters of Bertoxx server<BR>Master Brewer<BR>Master Drunk<BR>Master Baker (food and drink A Jesters must0</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE=